The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), President Muhammadu Buhari, is expected to visit Sokoto tomorrow (Wednesday) for the flag-off of his re-election campaign in the state. “Everything has also been diligently and efficiently put in place to make the all-important visit of President Muhammadu Buhari to the state, which is the indisputable trail blazer and pacesetter in Nigeria,” the Chairman, Northern Senators Forum, Senator Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko, disclosed in a statement by his media aide, Bashir Rabe Mani. He called on the people of Sokoto state to come out en masse to receive President Buhari. “The people of the state are reputed to be peace loving, while they are solidly behind the party, President Muhammadu Buhari, myself and APC’s gubernatorial candidate, Alhaji Ahmed Aliyu Sokoto, his running mate , Alhaji Faruku Malami Yabo, as well as other candidates, at all levels. “I am therefore extremely confident that, even now, the good people of the state will exhibit these  unparalleled love, support and cooperation by massively coming out to receive President Muhammadu Buhari and his entourage to the state,” he stated. Senate committee completes report on Amaechi, as Aishat faces opposition from Sokoto APC How states will vote Like Uyo, unlike Sokoto